               <p>DAVID SCOTT. I am clerk to Andrew Laughnan, who is a <rs id="t18180114-46-viclabel239" type="occupation">merchant</rs>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18180114-46-victim389 t18180114-46-viclabel239"></join>. On the 15th of December I was at Wool Quay seeing a cargo of wool landed. Stone, the officer, brought 2lbs of the wool down to me.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18180114-46-person390">
                  JOSEPH 
                  STONE
               <interp inst="t18180114-46-person390" type="surname" value="STONE"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18180114-46-person390" type="given" value="JOSEPH"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18180114-46-person390" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am officer. On the 15th of December I saw a cart, loaded with wool, stop at the bottom of Tower-street - Deacon drove it-the prisoner went to the tail-board, took some wool out of a bag, and put it in his breeches; I stopped him and took it from him. Several others were at the tail of the cart.</p>
               <p>JOHN DEACON. I drove the cart, which had ten bags of wool in it.</p>
               <p>Prisoner's Defence. I found it.</p>
               <p>
                  <rs id="t18180114-46-verdict240" type="verdictDescription">
                     <interp inst="t18180114-46-verdict240" type="verdictCategory" value="guilty"></interp>
               GUILTY
            </rs>. Aged 35.</p>
